data.database_description: The database is designed to manage and analyze electoral data within various counties. It includes details about each county such as its name, population, and zip code; political party information including elected officials for specific years; and election results at different district levels, noting which parties were represented and other relevant details like delegates and first elections. The schema links elections to specific counties through a district identifier and connects them to the respective political parties by referencing foreign keys, facilitating comprehensive tracking of electoral dynamics across regions. This setup allows stakeholders to gain insights into regional demographics, party performance over time, and election outcomes in relation to geographical locations.

columns.columnDescription: The total population in the county.
Postal code associated with the county.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about counties including their identification, name, population size, and zip code.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each party entry.
The year associated with the political data.
Name of the governor representing the party.
Name of the lieutenant governor associated with the party.
Name of the comptroller for the party.
Name of the attorney general representing the party.
Representative in the US Senate from the party, if applicable.

2, 2002.0, Liberal, Betsy McCaughey Ross, Jonathan Reiter, Alan Hevesi, Andrew Cuomo, (no election)

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains information about political parties, including year of data relevance and key officials such as governor, lieutenant governor, comptroller, attorney general, and US Senate representatives.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each election entry.
List of counties represented in the election.
Identifier linking to a specific county district.
Name and details of the elected delegate.
Reference to the party associated with the delegate, linked by Party_ID.
Year when the delegate was first elected.
Committee assignment of the elected delegate.
